Package data

Class Anime

java.lang.Object
data.Media
data.Anime
public class Anime extends Media
Defines an Anime object as a fundamental piece of the AnimeLog program. In this program, two anime cannot have the same name and year
Author:
Hunter Pruitt

    • Anime

      public Anime(String title, int year, int count, Anime.Language lan, Media.Type type, boolean finished, boolean dropped, String director, String studio, String notes)
      Constructor for an anime object, used when reading in data
      Parameters:
      title - name of entry
      year - release year for first episode
      count - number of episodes watched
      lan - language
      type - series or special
      finished - if the user finished watching
      dropped - if the user stopped watching
      director - director of the show
      studio - producers of the show
      notes - personal notes about the entry
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if passed bad parameters
